UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1284
1 AN ACT relating to domestic relations.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 403.240 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) If a party fails to comply with a provision of a decree or temporary order or
5 injunction, the obligation of the other party to make payments for support or
6 maintenance or to permit visitation or parenting time is not suspended; but a
7 party[he] may move the court to grant an appropriate order.
8 (2) The failure of either party, without good cause, to comply with a provision of a
9 decree or temporary order or injunction, including a provision with respect to
10 visitation, parenting time, or child support shall constitute contempt of court, and
11 the court shall remedy the failure to comply.
12 (3) Good cause for failure[not] to comply with a provision of a decree or temporary
13 order or injunction with respect to visitation or parenting time shall include:
14 (a) Mutual consent of the parties;[,]
15 (b) Reasonable belief by either party that there exists the possibility of
16 endangerment to the physical, mental, moral, or emotional health of the child,
17 or endangerment to the physical safety of either party;[,] or
18 (c) Extraordinary circumstances as determined by the court.
19 (4) The court may, if no reasonable cause is found for denial of visitation or parenting
20 time:[,]
21 (a) Order additional periods of visitation or parenting time to the prevailing
22 party. The additional periods of visitation or parenting time may:
23 1. Be of the same type and duration as the visitation or parenting time
24 that was denied;
25 2. Include weekend, holiday, and summer visitation or parenting time;
26 and
27 3. Be scheduled in accordance with the preference of the prevailing
