UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1284
1 party;
2 (b) Order that that the additional period of visitation or parenting time occur
3 within two (2) years of the date the court finds the party failed to comply
4 with a provision of a decree or temporary order or injunction with respect to
5 visitation or parenting time; and
6 (c) Award attorney's fees to the prevailing party.
7 (5) If a party's visitation or parenting time is temporarily suspended by a court order
8 based upon allegations of child abuse or neglect against the party, the court shall
9 order additional visitation or parenting time to the party whose time was
10 suspended if the Cabinet for Health and Family Services investigates and makes
11 no finding of abuse or neglect.
12 Section 2. This Act may be cited as the Time Taken Back Act.
